The paper deals with the problem of drawing directed acyclic graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents an integer programming model and a heuristic to solve the problem, which involves optimization and combinatorial aspects, making it relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and evaluations, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
